t</span></div></div></div><div class="slideshow-bottom" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.0.0.5"><div class="slide-meta-wrapper bottom-placement no-credit expanded" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.0.0.5.0"><span data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.0.0.5.0.1"></span><span class="component-toggle" aria-label="Toggle Button" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.0.0.5.0.2">Toggle</span><div class="slide-metadata" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.0.0.5.0.3"><div class="caption" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.0.0.5.0.3.0">Much of the country has already experienced winter&#39;s bone-chilling death grip. What much of the country needs now is a trip to the sauna. According to real scientists, sitting naked in a 150-degree room is probably better for you than you realize.

<p>&quot;In animal studies, warm temperature exposure—as you would get in a sauna—activates neurons that synthesize and release serotonin,&quot; a neurotransmitter important for emotional health, says Christopher Lowry, an associate professor of integrative physiology at the University of Colorado, Boulder. Translation: &quot;The more you sweat, the better you feel.&quot; Clinical studies also suggest that sweat <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21057782">flushes toxins</a> and that saunas <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11583886">improve cardiovascular function</a>.</p>

<p>Saunas are perhaps the best-known cultural export of Finland—a country of more than 5 million people and <a href="http://www.stat.fi/tup/suoluk/suoluk_asuminen_en.html">more 2 million saunas</a>, and a horribly cold place where folks have retreated to the steamy chambers for <a href="http://www.sauna.fi/in-english/sauna-information/sauna-in-finland/development-of-the-finnish-sauna/">two millennia</a>. And of course other cultures have their own versions. Thermal tubs like Japanese <a href="http://www.japan-guide.com/e/e2292.html">onsen</a>, for instance, could help <a href="http://www.japantimes.co.jp/community/2003/05/25/community/getting-into-hot-water-for-health/#.Uo0n9hZ3GHo">soothe joint pain</a>. Russian banyas are great for people who enjoy <a href="http://innamazing.wordpress.com/2012/07/09/what-is-a-russian-banya/">being beaten with tree limbs</a>.</p>

<p>To help you stay thawed out this winter, we offer this quick primer on Hot Rooms From Around The World (and where to find them in the USA). <a href="http://www.health.harvard.edu/press_releases/sauna_health_benefits">Some caveats</a> for you sweat hogs, though. The typical sauna-goer&#39;s pulse jumps 30 percent, so if you have heart arrhythmia, unstable angina, or advanced heart disease, you should probably stick to Snuggies. Also, be sure to cool down gradually post-sauna, and pound a few cups of water to stay hydrated. Prepare to sweat a pint or more in a single session; so basically the opposite of your usual relationship with a pint.</p></div><span data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.0.0.5.0.3.1"></span></div></div></div></main></div><div class="col col-md-6" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1"><aside class="slideshow-aside" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1.0"><div class="component-counter" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1.0.$slideshow-counter"><div class="counter" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1.0.$slideshow-counter.0"><span class="current" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1.0.$slideshow-counter.0.0">1</span><span class="divider" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1.0.$slideshow-counter.0.1">of</span><span class="total" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1.0.$slideshow-counter.0.2">6</span></div></div><span class="component-toggle toggle-thumbnails" aria-label="Toggle Button" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1.0.3">Toggle Thumbnails</span><div class="gqGalleryBox displayAd displayAd300x250 displayAd300x250Js gallery-aside-ad not-fetched hidden" id="gqGalleryBox300x250_frame" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.0.2.0.1.0.4:0"></div></aside></div></div></div></div><div class="gallery-bottom-container" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.1"><div class="col col-md-14 gallery-bottom-pane" data-reactid=".ua1qf5brb4.1:3.0.1.0"><div class="gqGalleryBan displayAd displayAd728x90 displayAd728x90Js gq-gallery-banner not-fetched hid